The paper deals with algorithms for computing various graph parameters in planar graphs, which are fundamental objects in computer science. The algorithms are based on techniques from graph theory, combinatorics, and numerical analysis, and involve sophisticated data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which covers research on efficient algorithms and data structures for solving computational problems. The paper also involves geometric and combinatorial aspects of planar graphs, such as their embedding, their connectivity, and their distances, which suggest that it could be relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Moreover, the paper uses numerical methods to approximate the distances and counts, which could be related to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), respectively. Overall, these five sub-categories seem to capture the main themes and techniques of the paper, and reflect its interdisciplinary nature.
